# k8s/svc-pricing/secrets.yaml.example
# ===========================================================================
# svc-pricing — Sub-Plan D (pricing extraction), INFRA deliverable I7.
#
# TEMPLATE ONLY — DO NOT commit a populated copy (playbook §0 / Section 10 Secret
# Management Discipline; no secret value in git).
#
# The svc-pricing Secret is named `svc-pricing-secrets` in the `dev` namespace.
# The single svc-pricing Deployment (api) consumes it via
# `envFrom: secretRef: { name: svc-pricing-secrets }` (see deployment.yaml).
# (There is NO worker — pricing has no Celery task.)
#
# Authority: handoff_msD_infra.md §1 I7 + spec_msD_backend §3.A (trimmed Settings)
# + MASTER_PLAN §5.D ("each service has its own trimmed Settings with ONLY the env
# vars it needs"). svc-pricing has the SMALLEST secret surface of any service.
#
# ── WHAT svc-pricing NEEDS (and ONLY this — 4 vars) ─────────────────────────
#   - DATABASE_URL   — points at the `pricing` schema (role=pricing_user).
#   - VALKEY_URL     — DB 0, RATE-LIMIT ONLY (the price_calc 600/h per-IP limiter,
#                      router.py:75 @rate_limit). pricing has NO Celery → NO broker/
#                      result DBs; NO cache layer beyond the rate-limit counter.
#   - JWT_SECRET     — LOCAL JWT verification (D7/A2: every service validates JWT
#                      locally via vendored core/auth.py; pricing does NOT call
#                      iam-svc per token). Shared HS256 secret from SM `jwt-secret`.
#   - APP_ENV        — Pydantic Settings Literal {development|staging|production}.
#
# ── WHAT svc-pricing MUST NOT RECEIVE (handoff §1 I7) ───────────────────────
#   NO CELERY_BROKER_URL / CELERY_RESULT_BACKEND (no worker — pricing has no task)
#   NO GEMINI_API_KEY / LANGFUSE_*  (no AI — pricing is deterministic P&L math)
#   NO GCS_* / GOOGLE_APPLICATION_CREDENTIALS (no storage — I6: no GCS, no SA)
#   NO MSG91_AUTH_KEY / MSG91_TEMPLATE_ID  (no SMS/OTP — that's iam-svc)
#   NO RAZORPAY_* / RAZORPAY_WEBHOOK_SECRET (no payment — that's iam-svc/billing)
#   NO REFRESH_TOKEN_PEPPER* / AUDIT_PII_SALT  (auth/pii concerns — iam-svc owns;
#     pricing's audit payload carries NO PII per MVP_ARCH §11.9)
#   This trimming is the §5.D blast-radius win: a compromised svc-pricing pod can
#   read NONE of the AI / SMS / payment / storage secrets — it is the lowest-value
#   target of any service (DB role scoped to one schema + a shared JWT verify key).
#
# ── DATABASE_URL — schema-scoped (MASTER_PLAN §2.D / §2.E) ───────────────────
#   Role = pricing_user (created by schema-role.sql, I5). search_path pins `pricing`
#   first then `public` (so the app sees its own tables AND public.audit_events).
#   asyncpg passes server options via the URL `options` query param, URL-encoded:
#     ?options=-csearch_path%3Dpricing,public
#   Host = postgres.dev.svc.cluster.local:5432 (the shared StatefulSet — V1.5 shares
#   one Postgres). The PgBouncer DATABASE_URL flip (to pgbouncer.dev.svc.cluster.local:6432)
#   is a SEPARATE founder-gated step (MS-0 step 3, blocked on backend R-MS-8) — NOT
#   in Sub-Plan D. Until then, dial postgres directly.
#   Password = the pricing_user password set out-of-band from SM (see I5) — the SAME
#   value used in ALTER ROLE pricing_user WITH PASSWORD. URL-encode any +,/,@ in the
#   password with urllib.parse.quote(pw, safe='') (MEMORY 2026-06-09 PG/Redis URL
#   parsing lesson — base64 passwords break URL parsing if embedded raw).
#
# ── VALKEY_URL (shared instance; DB 0 rate-limit only) ──────────────────────
#   svc-pricing's VALKEY_URL hits the SAME shared Valkey instance as the monolith,
#   DB 0 (sessions + OTP + rate-limits). pricing uses ONLY the rate-limit keyspace
#   (the price_calc per-IP sliding window). NO broker (DB 1) / result (DB 2) / cache
#   (DB 3) — pricing has no Celery and no cache. The rate-limit keys are app-prefixed
#   in the vendored rate_limit_mw code (not here).
#
# Populate from GCP Secret Manager (project=project-1f5cbf72-2820-4cdb-949):
#   JWT_SECRET            ← SM `jwt-secret`            (gcloud secrets versions access latest --secret=jwt-secret)
#   pricing_user password ← SM `dev-pricing-db-password` (NEW SM secret — founder to
#                            create at bootstrap; SAME value used in I5 ALTER ROLE)
#                            ⚠ INTER-LEAD/founder: this is the ONE new SM secret
#                            Sub-Plan D needs. It is a per-service DB password, NOT a
#                            new IAM grant — within the §4 ceiling. Founder creates
#                            the SM container + version; infra composes it into
#                            DATABASE_URL. (Mirrors svc-export's dev-export-db-password
#                            + svc-image's dev-image-db-password.)
# ===========================================================================
apiVersion: v1
kind: Secret
metadata:
  name: svc-pricing-secrets
  namespace: dev
type: Opaque
stringData:
  # --- Database (schema-scoped to `pricing`, role pricing_user) ---
  DATABASE_URL: "postgresql+asyncpg://pricing_user:REPLACE-ME@postgres.dev.svc.cluster.local:5432/meesell?options=-csearch_path%3Dpricing,public"

  # --- Valkey (SHARED instance; DB 0 RATE-LIMIT ONLY — no broker/result/cache) ---
  VALKEY_URL: "redis://:REPLACE-ME@valkey.dev.svc.cluster.local:6379/0"

  # --- JWT (LOCAL verification per D7/A2; shared HS256 secret from SM jwt-secret) ---
  JWT_SECRET: "REPLACE-ME-FROM-SM-jwt-secret"

  # --- App env (Pydantic Literal: development|staging|production) ---
  # dev namespace ⇒ "development" (MEMORY: NEVER "dev"; the Literal type rejects it).
  APP_ENV: "development"

  # --- DELIBERATELY ABSENT (handoff §1 I7): CELERY_BROKER_URL, CELERY_RESULT_BACKEND
  #     (no worker), GEMINI_API_KEY, LANGFUSE_SECRET_KEY, GCS_* /
  #     GOOGLE_APPLICATION_CREDENTIALS (I6 — no GCS, no SA), MSG91_AUTH_KEY,
  #     MSG91_TEMPLATE_ID, RAZORPAY_KEY_ID, RAZORPAY_KEY_SECRET,
  #     RAZORPAY_WEBHOOK_SECRET, REFRESH_TOKEN_PEPPER*, AUDIT_PII_SALT. ---
